main event: On 25 January 1953, a resident in Baronette, Wisconsin, reported sighting a flying object described as approximately 10 feet in diameter, white and blue in color, traveling at high speed.
interesting points: The object appeared to be controlled as it made a sudden stop,It was observed for about 10 minutes,The object had a bluish-green glow when it disappeared into a cloud,The conclusion of the report suggested it could have been astronomical, possibly a star,It was reported one day earlier than the final summary date.
sighted object: flying object approximately 10 feet in diameter, white and blue in color
